The Contractor for the I-0911A project (I-40 over the Yadkin River at the Davie-Forsyth County Line) plans&nbsp;to close a ramp at NC 801 (Exit 180) near Bermuda Run on Tuesday February 23rd. The contractor will close the on-ramp from NC 801 to I-40 Westbound overnight from 9:00PM - 9:00AM. A detour will be utilized for this ramp closure. A link to the detour map is provided below. The contractor will utilize this ramp closure to safely install a drainage system pipe across the ramp. This work is part of the&nbsp;continuing construction to&nbsp;replace the I-40 bridges over the Yadkin River and to widen and make improvements along I-40.&nbsp;As always this work is weather dependent and may be subject to change.
